
## Our Pledge

In the spirit of building a Better Humanity, we commit to creating a welcoming, respectful, and inclusive community for all contributors and users. We pledge to treat everyone with kindness, dignity, and fairness.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

- Using welcoming and inclusive language  
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences  
- Gracefully accepting constructive criticism  
- Focusing on what is best for the community  
- Showing empathy towards other community members  

Examples of unacceptable behavior by participants include:

- Harassment, discrimination, or exclusion based on race, gender, sexual orientation, disability, religion, or any other personal characteristic  
- Intimidation, threats, or derogatory comments  
- Public or private harassment  
- Disruptive or harmful behavior that impedes community collaboration  

## Enforcement Responsibilities

Community leaders are responsible for clarifying standards and enforcing the Code of Conduct fairly and consistently.

## Reporting Guidelines

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it by opening an issue marked **confidential** or contacting the maintainers via Discord privately.

All reports will be handled with discretion and respect for privacy.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies within project spaces, public and private communications, and community events.

## Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may result in temporary or permanent bans from the community or repository, at the discretion of the leadership team.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/), version 2.1.

---

Thank you for helping create a welcoming environment to build a Better Humanity.
